<p><pb

n="1v"/><!--
This is not explicitly stated anywhere I've read, but I assume that these double plates, each inscribed on one face only, use 1verso and 2 recto, with the blank side of each plate facing outward.
--><lb
n="1"/><g type="mangala"/>svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> Uccakalpān mahārāja-ogha<space type="binding-hole"/>devas tasya puttras tat-pādānudhyāto mahā<!--
The maṅgala symbol seems to be shaped like a figure 9 with the tail extended. The head is not quite clear on the facsimile.
--><lb
n="2" break="no"/>devyāṁ kumāradevyām utpanno mahārāja-<space type="binding-hole"/>kumāradevas tasya puttras tat-pād<unclear>ā</unclear>nudhyāt<choice><sic>e</sic><corr>o</corr></choice>
<lb
n="3"/>mahādevyāṁ jayasvāminyām utpanno mah<unclear>ā</unclear>rāja-jayasvāmī tasya puttras tat-pād<unclear>ā</unclear>nudhyāt<choice><sic>e</sic><corr>o</corr></choice> <lb
n="4"/>mah<unclear>ā</unclear>devy<unclear>āṁ</unclear> rāmadevyām utpanno mahārāja-vy<unclear>ā</unclear>ghras tasya puttras tat-pādānudhyāto mahā<lb
n="5" break="no"/>devyām ajjhitadevyām utpanno mahārāja-jayanāthaḥ kuśalī nāgadeya-santaka-cha<lb
n="6" break="no"/>ndāpallikāyāṁ brāhmaṇādīn kuṭumbinaḥ kārukāṁś ca samājñāpayati</p>
<p><sic>vadataṁm bo</sic> stu <lb
n="7"/>yathaiṣa grāmo mayā svapuṇyābhivr̥ddhaye kāṇva-sagottra-vājasaneya-mādhya<!--
Fleet reads (or at least prints) kāṇva instead of kaṇva. The ā mātrā is clear in the facsimile.
--><lb
n="8" break="no"/>ndi<unclear>n</unclear>a-brāhmaṇa-mittrasvāminaḥ sodraṅgaḥ sopar<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>i</corr></choice>karaḥ A-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśyaḥ<!--
Fleet reads mādhyandina without comment, but the character is not like na at all (compare svāminaḥ in this line), instead it looks most like kta (compare l13). Assuming that it looks better in the original (na, with the loop damaged, does look like ka in several places in this charter and IN00083), I accept Fleet's reading.
--><!--
Fleet also prints soparikaraḥ without comment, but the I mātrā is completely missing in the facsimile. Since similar errors occur elsewhere in the plate, I take this to be a scribal error.
--><lb
n="9"/>cora-varjjito tisr̥ṣṭas<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> te yūyam asya samucita-bhāga-bhoga-kara-pratyāyopa<lb
n="10" break="no"/>nayaṁ ka<choice><sic>ka</sic><corr>ri</corr></choice>ṣyatha Ājñā-śravaṇa-vidheyāś ca bhaviṣyatha</p>
<p>ye cāsmad-va<sic>n</sic>śotpadya<lb
n="11" break="no"/>mānaka-rājānas tair iyaṁ dattir nna vilopyānumodanīyā samucita-rājā<lb
n="12" break="no"/>bhāvya-kara-pratyāyā na grāhyāḥ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> yaś caināṁ dattiṁ lopayeT sa pañcabhiḥ<!--
Fleet understands rāja-a-bhāvya, "taxes which by custom should not belong to the king". I'm not sure about this but haven't checked. If we take rājā as standing for rāja, then there should be a hyphen at the end of the line and the lb should be a breaking element.
--><!--
The halanta T is practically full-sized, with a dash above it.
--><pb

n="2r"/><lb
n="13"/>mahā-pātakair upapātakaiś ca saṁyu<space type="binding-hole"/>kta<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> syā<sic>n</sic><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> uktaṁ ca mahābhārate bhagavatā<lb
n="14"/>vyāsena</p>
<lg n="1" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">sva-dattāṁ para-dattāṁ vā</l>
<l n="b">yatnād rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira</l>
<l n="c">mahīm mahīmatāṁ <lb
n="15"/>śreṣṭha</l>
<l n="d">dānāc chreyo nupālanaṁ</l>
</lg>
<lg n="2" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">bahubhir vvasudhā bhuktā</l>
<l n="b">rājabhiḥ sagarādibhiḥ</l>
<l n="c">yasya <lb
n="16"/>yasya yadā bhūmis</l>
<l n="d">tasya tasya tadā phalaṁ</l>
</lg>
<lg n="3" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">prāyeṇa hi narendrāṇāṁ</l>
<l n="b">vidyate nā<lb
n="17" break="no"/>śubhā gatiḥ</l>
<l n="c">pūyante te tu satataṁ</l>
<l n="d">prayacchanto vasundharāṁ<!--
Fleet prints pūyānte, probably a typo. The text is, correctly, pūyante.
--></l>
</lg>
<lg n="4" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">ṣaṣṭi-varṣa-sahasrā<lb
n="18" break="no"/><unclear>ṇi</unclear></l>
<l n="b"><unclear>svargge</unclear> modati bhūmidaḥ</l>
<l n="c">Acchettā cānumantā ca</l>
<l n="d">tāny eva narake vaseT<!--
The halanta T is practically full size, with a line above.
--></l>
</lg>
<lg n="5" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a"><lb
n="19"/><unclear>āspho</unclear>ṭa<choice><sic>l</sic><corr>y</corr></choice>anti pitaraḥ</l>
<l n="b">pravalganti pitāmahāḥ</l>
<l n="c">bhūmido sma<supplied reason="omitted">t</supplied>-kule jātaḥ</l>
<l n="d">sa n<sic>o</sic> <lb
n="20"/>ttrā<unclear>tā bhaviṣya</unclear>ti<!--
The halanta T is practically full size, with a line above.
--></l>
</lg>
<lg n="6" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">sarvva-sasya-samr̥ddhā<sic>n</sic> tu</l>
<l n="b">yo hareta vasundharāṁ</l>
<l n="c">śva-viṣṭhāyāṁ kr̥mi<lb
n="21" break="no"/>r bhūtvā</l>
<l n="d"><unclear>pitr̥bhis sa</unclear>ha majjati|<!--
The punctuation sign appears to be a short horizontal dash, faint, short, and low down, roughly at the baseline of standard-sized characters.
--></l>
</lg>
<p>sambatsara-<choice><sic>g</sic><corr>ś</corr></choice>ate catuḥ-saptate Āṣāḍha-māsa<lb
n="22" break="no"/>sya caturddaśa<unclear>me d</unclear>ivase<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> Asyāṁ divasa-pūrvvāyāṁ likhitaṁ mayā bhogika-rājyi<lb
n="23" break="no"/>lāmātya-naptr̥-<unclear>bhog</unclear>ika-dhruvadatta-puttra-bhogika-guñjakīrttinā<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> <choice><sic>dūtakoparika</sic><corr>dūtaka Uparika</corr></choice><lb
n="24" break="no"/>-dīkṣita-gr̥hapati-sthapati-samrāṭ ccharvvadatta Iti||</p><!--
The punctuation sign is a double vertical; the top of the first one is hooked to the left.
--><p>sambat <num value="174"><g type="numeral">100</g> <g type="numeral">70</g> 4</num>āṣā<lb
n="25" break="no"/>ḍha di <num value="14"><g type="numeral">10</g> 4</num>|<!--
The halanta T (ta with dash) is quite small, but this is probably because dū in the previous line extends quite far down.
--><!--
Line 25 begins at about 1/3 the length of the plate, approximately below pa of sthapati. As the corners are rounded, there would have been no room to start this line at the edge of the plate, but it could have been started 3 or 4 characters to the right of the margin if the inscriber had wanted to.
--><!--
The final punctuation sign is a long horizontal dash.
--></p>
